data.chText: 连绵不断的雨把土地淋了个透。
data.enText: The continuous rain had saturated the soil.
to fill sth/sb completely with sth so that it is impossible or useless to add any more

data.chText: 那家公司的产品已使电子记事簿市场饱和。
data.enText: The company had saturated the market for personal organizers (= so that no new buyers could be found) .

simple_means.memory_skill: satur 足够，饱足 + ate 使… → 使足够 → 使饱和

tr: cause (a chemical compound, vapour, solution, magnetic material) to unite with the greatest possible amount of another substance

value.def: If people or things saturate a place or object, they fill it completely so that no more can be added.

example.ex: In the last days before the vote, both sides are saturating the airwaves...
example.tran: 选举前最后几天，竞选双方占用了所有的广播电台和电视台。

example.ex: As the market was saturated with goods and the economy became more balanced, inflation went down.
example.tran: 随着市场上商品饱和，经济趋于平衡，通货膨胀就减弱了。

example.ex: As the domestic market becomes saturated, firms begin to export the product.
example.tran: 由于国内市场饱和，各公司开始外销。

value.def: If someone or something is saturated, they become extremely wet.

example.ex: If the filter has been saturated with motor oil, it should be discarded and replaced.
example.tran: 过滤器如果已被机油浸透，则应丢弃并换上新的。

example.ex: His work clothes, having become saturated with oil, had to be cleaned.
example.tran: 他的工作服已经被油浸透，该洗洗了。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = enough, full of food 足够, 饱足
rootsaffixes.title: sat(i), satis, satur

partsOfSpeech.dec: in 不 + satiate 使充分满足 → 不满足的
sat 足够，饱足 + e → 使饱足
sati 足够，饱足 + able 可…的 → 可满足的
sati 足够，饱足 + ate 使… → 使充分满足
satis 足够，饱足 + fy 使… → 使满足
satis 足够，饱足 + faction 形成… → 满足
satur 足够，饱足 + ate 使… → 使足够 → 使饱和
satur 足够，饱足 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 饱和
